@startuml ATM_State_Transitions

[*] --> NoCardState

NoCardState --> HasCardState: insertCard()
NoCardState --> NoCardState: ejectCard()\nenterPin()\nwithdrawCash()

HasCardState --> NoCardState: ejectCard()
HasCardState --> CashWithdrawalState: enterPin(1234)
HasCardState --> HasCardState: insertCard()\nwithdrawCash()
HasCardState --> HasCardState: enterPin(invalid)

CashWithdrawalState --> NoCardState: ejectCard()
CashWithdrawalState --> CashWithdrawalState: insertCard()\nenterPin()\nwithdrawCash()

NoCardState --> [*]

note right of NoCardState
    Initial State
    - No card inserted
    - Only insertCard() is valid
    - Other operations print error
end note

note right of HasCardState
    Card Inserted
    - Card is in the machine
    - PIN not yet verified
    - Valid: ejectCard(), enterPin()
    - Invalid: insertCard(), withdrawCash()
end note

note right of CashWithdrawalState
    PIN Verified
    - User can withdraw cash
    - Valid: withdrawCash(), ejectCard()
    - Invalid: insertCard(), enterPin()
    - Uses Chain of Responsibility
      for cash processing
end note

@enduml
